+**Precise definition of "progress"** (to avoid a partial-livelock where one
+counter advances while the experiment is wedged): progress = `completed`
+strictly increased **or** `open_tasks + in_flight` strictly decreased since
+the previous heartbeat. A heartbeat where only `iteration` advances (same
+task counts) is **not** progress — that is the stuck signature. The smoke
+quiescence-wait asserts on this delta, not on `iteration` alone. On timeout,
+the script dumps the heartbeat series, so the failure report says "stuck at
+4 open / 0 completed for 120 s" vs "completing ~1 task / 8 s, just slow" —
+turning every future timeout into a self-diagnosing failure. This is the
+single highest-leverage change: it does not *prevent* the next quiescence
+break, but it makes every one legible in the CI log without a local repro.
